She told the Daily Telegraph: 'It has been on and on for years. Loud music, people coming and going very late, talking in the road, shouting, cars arriving, cars going. It's like having a nightclub on your doorstep in the middle of a quiet terraced street. 

'I have written to "Violet no-manners" as we call her, several times and sent text messages. Sometimes she apologises but it doesn't stop. Around early February  I wrote to the Duke. He wrote back a short letter which was perfectly courteous and said he had made the "occupants" aware of its contents.' 

However, Lady Victoria, whose father is worth an estimated £125 million, uploaded the letter onto the internet. 

Mrs Elliot continued: 'It is typical of the immaturity and lack of manners they have. We are highly tolerant, relaxed neighbours but we are living somewhere where you can't get a decent night's sleep. I don't know what they do, it's like they have elephants in the house.'

